<section id="about">
  <h2>What I Do</h2>
  <p>
    I'm a Senior AI Engineer at Consensys, where I build AI-powered products
    used by hundreds of thousands of users — RAG-powered search systems, AI
    agents, automated data pipelines, and end-to-end support automation. Outside
    of that I study what AI adoption is doing to human judgment and capability —
    and I'm building something to help people use these tools without quietly
    losing what makes them good at their jobs.
  </p>

  <h2>My Why</h2>
  <p>
    I believe technology should be at the service of a more human life. AI,
    blockchain, and emerging systems only create value when they are used with
    intention. My focus is on the intersection of technology and neuroscience —
    understanding how the tools we use shape the way we think, for better and
    for worse. <b>Tech is not the goal—people are.</b> When used consciously, technology
    becomes a tool that frees energy instead of consuming it.
  </p>

  <h2>What I Love</h2>
  <p>
    Outside work you'll find me learning nerdy things, moving my body, spending
    time in nature, doing manual crafts, traveling, or making homemade desserts.
    I love connecting with curious minds who care about technology and making
    things that actually matter — whether that's to collaborate, exchange ideas,
    or just have a good conversation.
  </p>

  <div class="signature">
    <p>— Sara</p>
  </div>
</section>

